---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body class="about-page">
    <Header />
    <main class="container">

      <section class="hero">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
      </section>

      <section class="about">
        <h2>Why this platform exists</h2>
        <p>Mind the Gael exists because i've seen, and personally experienced, how limited and inconsistent access to sports psychology support can be more female athletes. </p>
        <p>For many of us, mental performance education only shows up in small moments, maybe a team workshop here and there, or through private support that isn’t always accessible due to time, cost, or opportunity.</p>
        <p>And that creates a gap. A gap in understanding confidence, pressure, focus, anxiety, and mental wellbeing in sport, right when athletes need that understanding the most.</p>
        <p>Mind the Gael exists to help bridge that gap.</p>
        <p>Just to be really clear, I am not a sports psychologist. This platform is not clinical advice or therapy. What I share here is based on my own lived experience as an athlete, alongside research I’m actively learning from, exploring, and translating into language that makes sense in real sport.</p>
        <p>My aim is education and awareness,helping athletes better understand their minds, not diagnosing or treating anything.</p>
        
        <h2>The Problem I'm Focused On</h2>
        <p>This platform comes directly from my own experience as an athlete. For a long time, I struggled to understand what was happening in my own mind in sport. I experienced moments of anxiety, overthinking, loss of confidence, and pressure that I didn’t fully know how to make sense of at the time.</p>
        <p>And what I realised was that I didn’t just need “motivation” or generic advice, I needed a clearer understanding of how my mind was actually working in those moments, and practical ways to deal with it when it showed up on the pitch.
        <p>That’s what Mind the Gael is built around.</p>
        <p>This platform focuses on what it actually feels like in training and match situations, when your mind drifts, when pressure builds, when confidence shifts, and when performance doesn’t reflect what you know you’re capable of.
        <p>The goal here is simple: to make the mental side of sport easier to understand, and more usable in real time, based on lived experience and psychological learning translated into practical language.</p>


        <h2>What will I find here?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Sports psychology explained in a simple, practical way</li>
          <li>Mental performance tools for training and match day</li>
          <li>Insights into focus, confidence, pressure and decision making</li>
          <li>Understanding of what actually happens in your mind during sport</li>
          <li>Research and psychological concepts translated into real playing situations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Is this platform for me?</h2>
        <p> This is for female athletes, coaches, and support staff who want to better understand the mental side of performance.</p>
         <p>It’s for those who want to:</p>
          <ul>
             <li>perform more consistently under pressure</li>
             <li>build confidence in key moments</li>
             <li>Understand how mindset affects focus and decision-making</li>
             <li>Make sense of what you’re experiencing mentally in sport.</li>
             <li>Support your own wellbeing, and know when to seek further help if needed</li>
             <li>Or if you’re involved in player development or coaching and want a clearer understanding of sports psychology in action.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

        <h2>Start here</h2>
        <div class="start-buttons">
          <a href="/blog/training-the-mind/" class="start-button">Training the Mind</a>
          <a href="/blog/gael-performance-toolkit/" class="start-button">Gael Performance Toolkit</a>
          <a href="/blog/strong-minds-stronger-players/" class="start-button">Strong Minds, Stronger Players</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  h1 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about p,
  .honest p,
  .what-we-build p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .honest {
    border-left: 3px solid #69005a;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .what-we-build ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .what-we-build ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about ul {
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .closing {
    color: #f0cdff;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .start-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .start-button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.2rem;
    background-color: var(--green-lime);
    color: var(--green-dark);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .start-button:hover {
    background-color: var(--purple-light);
    border-color: var(--purple);
    color: var(--green-dark);
  }

</style>
